theorem Topology.interior_inter_open_left {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {U A : Set X}
    (hU : IsOpen (U : Set X)) :
    interior ((U ∩ A) : Set X) = U ∩ interior (A : Set X) := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · intro x hx
    rcases hx with ⟨V, hV_open, hxV, hV_subset⟩
    have hxU : x ∈ U := (hV_subset hxV).1
    have hV_subsetA : (V : Set X) ⊆ A := by
      intro y hy
      exact (hV_subset hy).2
    have hxIntA : x ∈ interior (A : Set X) :=
      ⟨V, hV_open, hxV, hV_subsetA⟩
    exact ⟨hxU, hxIntA⟩
  · intro x hx
    rcases hx with ⟨hxU, hxIntA⟩
    rcases hxIntA with ⟨V, hV_open, hxV, hV_subsetA⟩
    have hVU_open : IsOpen ((V ∩ U) : Set X) := hV_open.inter hU
    have hxVU : x ∈ V ∩ U := ⟨hxV, hxU⟩
    have h_subset : (V ∩ U : Set X) ⊆ U ∩ A := by
      intro y hy
      have hyV : y ∈ V := hy.1
      have hyU : y ∈ U := hy.2
      have hyA : y ∈ A := hV_subsetA hyV
      exact ⟨hyU, hyA⟩
    exact ⟨V ∩ U, hVU_open, hxVU, h_subset⟩

theorem Topology.closureInterior_eq_self_of_isClopen {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} (hA_open : IsOpen (A : Set X)) (hA_closed : IsClosed (A : Set X)) :
    closure (interior (A : Set X)) = A := by
  have h_int : interior (A : Set X) = A := hA_open.interior_eq
  have h_cl : closure (A : Set X) = A := hA_closed.closure_eq
  simpa [h_int, h_cl]
